# Demo Workflow Guide

This guide defines the standard demo-generation workflow for Onto2AI demos.

The current standard is the introduction demo: a script-driven, presentation-rendered video with OpenAI `cedar` narration. The workflow keeps durable source files in `demo/`, writes temporary render frames and video segments to the system temp directory, and publishes only the final reusable assets.

## Standard Folder Structure

- `demo/introduction/` - source and generation workflow for the Onto2AI introduction demo.
- `demo/introduction/introduction-script.md` - long-form narration and story source.
- `demo/introduction/generate_introduction_video.py` - canonical generator for the introduction video.
- `demo/introduction/render_introduction_template_deck.mjs` - presentation artifact-tool renderer for the LinkedIn-style deck.
- `demo/introduction/assets/` - durable local visual inputs used by the generator.
- `demo/introduction/*.pptx` - editable source/template decks.
- `demo/audio/*.mp3` - generated narration clips.
- `demo/video/<demo_name>/<demo_name>_demo.json` - single source of truth manifest for a generated demo.
- `demo/video/<demo_name>/*_narration.txt` - manifest-derived narration text.
- `demo/video/review/*.mp4` - review/final video exports.

## Introduction Demo

The introduction demo is the reference implementation for future demos.

Durable inputs:
- `demo/introduction/introduction-script.md`
- `demo/introduction/assets/onto2ai-qa-frontpage-4.png`
- `demo/introduction/onto2ai-linkedin-presentation-template.pptx`
- `demo/introduction/generate_introduction_video.py`
- `demo/introduction/render_introduction_template_deck.mjs`

Generated deliverables:
- `demo/introduction/onto2ai-introduction-template-video-deck.pptx`
- `demo/audio/onto2ai_introduction_cedar.mp3`
- `demo/video/introduction/introduction_demo.json`
- `demo/video/introduction/introduction_narration.txt`
- `demo/video/review/onto2ai_introduction_template.mp4`

## Regenerate Introduction Video

Reuse the existing OpenAI `cedar` narration:

```bash
python3 demo/introduction/generate_introduction_video.py
```

Refresh the OpenAI `cedar` narration and rebuild the video:

```bash
export OPENAI_API_KEY="your_openai_key"
python3 demo/introduction/generate_introduction_video.py --refresh-audio
```

Keep scratch frames and segment files for debugging:

```bash
python3 demo/introduction/generate_introduction_video.py --keep-work
```

Scratch output is written under the system temp directory, not under `demo/`.

## Single Source Of Truth

Use `*_demo.json` as the canonical per-demo production file:

- `narrative_lines[].text` - authoritative narration text.
- `narrative_lines[].start_ms` / `end_ms` - scene timing.
- `slides[]` - presentation content.
- `output_audio` - narration artifact path.
- `output_video` - review video artifact path.

This avoids drift between scripts, rendered decks, narration files, and video exports.

## Audio Standard

Use OpenAI TTS with:

- model: `gpt-4o-mini-tts-2025-12-15`
- voice: `cedar`
- format: `mp3`

The introduction generator already wraps the standard TTS command. For one-off audio generation, use the shared speech CLI:

```bash
python /Users/weizhang/.codex/skills/speech/scripts/text_to_speech.py speak \
  --model gpt-4o-mini-tts-2025-12-15 \
  --input-file demo/video/introduction/introduction_narration.txt \
  --voice cedar \
  --response-format mp3 \
  --instructions "Voice Affect: Warm and composed. Tone: Professional and clear. Pacing: Steady." \
  --out demo/audio/onto2ai_introduction_cedar.mp3 \
  --force
```

## Video Standard

For presentation-style demos:

1. Build or update the `*_demo.json` manifest.
2. Generate or reuse the `cedar` narration MP3.
3. Render an editable deck to slide frames using the presentation artifact tool.
4. Assemble frames into a silent MP4 in temp.
5. Mux narration into `demo/video/review/<demo_name>.mp4`.
6. Verify with `ffprobe` before sharing.

Expected introduction output:

```text
1280x720, 30fps, 92.4s, H.264 video, AAC audio
```

## Future Screen-Recording Demos

For UI walkthroughs based on raw recordings, keep the same conventions:

- raw recording under `demo/video/<demo_name>/`
- one manifest at `demo/video/<demo_name>/<demo_name>_demo.json`
- narration under `demo/audio/`
- final review export under `demo/video/review/`

Do not scatter generated scripts, frame dumps, or temporary segment files under the repository. Keep reusable sources and deliverables only.

## Notes

- Narration audio is AI-generated and should be disclosed when presented externally.
- Keep all demo artifacts under `demo/`.
- Prefer deterministic file names so demos can be regenerated and compared.
